    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Add LVI variable from Openclinica to primary site surgery functions to pull in and harmonize with registry source (prioritize MA over registry to future proof when we eventually receive registry data for these patients)</p>

<p><b>Restrict LVI values from OpenClinica to patients diagnosed 2024+ for use in this function as those patients should not have had OpenClinica prepopulation for this variable and the “recency approach” was looking for patients diagnosed 2024 and forward.</b></p>



<hr />

<p>Archived </p>

<p>LVI under recency abstraction rules is captured in a variable in openclinica that was once used for pre-population and abandoned. However, I cannot delineate between data which exists for recency abstracted patients versus pre-pop. If I have a delineating date OR a list of patients who I know were targeted for recency abstraction, I can finish development.</p>



<p>Context: <a href="https://syapse.slack.com/archives/CEFHN97EY/p1765831850723029" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://syapse.slack.com/archives/CEFHN97EY/p1765831850723029</a> </p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Comments</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" class="grid" style="margin: 0;">
                <tr id="comment-header-362781"><td bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
            Comment by  
                                                    
                
        
            <a class="user-hover" rel="712020:75ed883e-1be1-4ae4-b866-8058b00676df"
                id="word_commented_712020:75ed883e-1be1-4ae4-b866-8058b00676df"
                href="https://n-power.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A75ed883e-1be1-4ae4-b866-8058b00676df">
                    Kaitlyn Kane (Inactive)
                </a>

                                        <font size="-2">
            [
                <font color="#336699">20/Feb/26</font>

                            ]
            </font>

        </td></tr>
        <tr id="comment-body-362781"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p><a href="https://n-power.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A90ff19f2-8b5e-4277-ae46-f117e454bd84" class="user-hover" rel="712020:90ff19f2-8b5e-4277-ae46-f117e454bd84" data-account-id="712020:90ff19f2-8b5e-4277-ae46-f117e454bd84" accountid="712020:90ff19f2-8b5e-4277-ae46-f117e454bd84" rel="noreferrer">Rebecca Hodge</a> the task here is to add the LVI variable from openclinica sources to the primary site surgery function  </p>

<p>The comment in the description refers to the issue in the slack thread - essentially, </p>

<ul>
	<li>OpenClinica was at one point using registry data to prepopulate this variable but records in the OpenClinica changelog and from Ronda show that was supposed to have been discontinued.
	<ul>
		<li>Issue #1 is that it seems some patients still have data in this field as there are patients diagnosed/abstracted in years prepopulation was supposed to be turned off (this isn’t a field that is currently part of OpenClinica GUTS abstraction)</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>When the Guidance was updated for the “recency approach” (meaning, patients loaded into OpenClinica without a registry file from AI team or other structured sources) - a new variable for LVI was not created - they simply started using the preexisting one
	<ul>
		<li>Issue #2 - we can delineate prepopulated data versus data we know was collected by the abstraction team</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>


<p>We are worried about this given these macro pre-populated data considerations in OpenClinica due to which we do not use pre-populated data fields that are not part of general abstraction guidance for the ODS team to update since the data is highly at risk of being irrelevant to the patient and/or less correct than another registry source</p>

<ol>
	<li>There was a pre-population bug that affected OpenClinica where values from other patients records cross pollinated - they could not correct the issue without major lift, so that data exists still, with no real way of telling who was affected or not (I tried)</li>
	<li>We do not have visibility on which registry file was used to pre-populate a record (a subset of patients can have multiple depending on if they received diagnostics at one location and treatment elsewhere). Given our prioritization logic prioritized MA over registry when both are available, this could bake in some mis-priortization of records if better data were available from a different registry file (lower risk)</li>
</ol>


<p>All of this to say, barring an indicator per patient to indicate if they were loaded via “recency” approach versus “registry”, we don’t have a clean way to delineate these data. I had a ticket out to create such an indicator, but there isn’t enough existing infrastructure on other teams to provide us the information we would need to build and maintain that variable. </p>

<p>Instead, <b>a reasonable approach here would be to pull in LVI values for patients diagnosed 2024+ for use in this function as those patients should not have had OpenClinica prepopulation for this variable and the “recency approach” was looking for patients diagnosed 2024 and forward.</b></p>
        </td></tr>
            </table>
